OL,3,CSEND reform: Delayed government
OL,4,CSchools White Paper to be published
OL,6,FLast week, ITV News reported that
OL,7,Fparents and carers of SEND children
OL,8,Fare being pushed to the brink by a
OL,9,Fbroken system and left with no choice
OL,10,Fbut to give up their employment to
OL,11,Fadvocate for their children.
OL,13,FParents told us they are increasingly
OL,14,Fbeing "forced" to quit their jobs,
OL,15,Freduce their hours or take out loans,
OL,16,Fas overstretched and under-resourced
OL,17,Fschools struggle to support students
OL,18,Fwith additional needs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1771909410
OL,3,CSEND reform: Delayed government
OL,4,CSchools White Paper to be published
OL,6,FThe government's major overhaul of the
OL,7,FSEND system comes at a point of
OL,8,Ftension for many families who feel let
OL,9,Fdown by authorities and are
OL,10,Fincreasingly apprehensive of what's to
OL,11,Fcome.
OL,13,FCathy Wassell, CEO of Autistic Girls
OL,14,FNetwork, is among those concerned
OL,15,Fabout the Schools White Paper,
OL,16,Fdescribing the expected government
OL,17,Fannouncements as "a betrayal of the
OL,18,Fvery principle of inclusion".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1771909410
OL,3,CSEND reform: Delayed government
OL,4,CSchools White Paper to be published
OL,6,F"This White Paper represents a
OL,7,Ftargeted strike on an invisible
OL,8,Fpopulation," she told ITV News.
OL,10,F"By drastically reducing support at
OL,11,Fthe secondary level, the government is
OL,12,Fcreating a cliff-edge for thousands of
OL,13,Fneurodivergent young people who have
OL,14,Fspent their primary years 'masking'
OL,15,Ftheir distress just to survive.
OL,17,F"Autistic girls often spend primary
OL,18,Fschool masking their struggles. They
OL,19,Fonly get identified when they hit the
OL,20,F'secondary crash.'
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1771909410
OL,3,CSEND reform: Delayed government
OL,4,CSchools White Paper to be published
OL,6,F"Slashing support now is like removing
OL,7,Fa life jacket just as the child is
OL,8,Fpulled into the deep end," she added.
OL,10,FMeanwhile teaching unions have also
OL,11,Fbeen critical of the expected reforms,
OL,12,Farguing that teachers' voices have
OL,13,Fbeen "conspicuously absent" from the
OL,14,Fdecision-making.
OL,16,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,17,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,18,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,19,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1771909410
OL,3,CSEND reform: Delayed government
OL,4,CSchools White Paper to be published
OL,6,FMatt Wrack, general secretary of
OL,7,FNASUWT The Teachers' Union, said:
OL,8,F"Teachers are already expected to be
OL,9,Fsocial workers, counsellors and
OL,10,Fsecurity guards, and now it seems they
OL,11,Fmay be required to fill other gaps in
OL,12,Fthe system without adequate support.
OL,14,F"Teachers have many talents, but they
OL,15,Fcannot overcome a decade of systemic
OL,16,Funderfunding or growing SEND needs
OL,17,Fwith a bit of extra training."
OL,19,FHowever, others remain cautiously
OL,20,Foptimistic that the reforms could be
OL,21,Fpositive for schools.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
